            <p data-aos="flip-up" data-aos-once="true" data-aos-duration="700">
              August 16th, 2013, the day of my birthday, I arrived on Belmont's campus. Over three years later, Belmont
              was the home of the most intensive period of growth I've been through. With a major in computer science and a
              minor in entrepreneurship, no part of my brain has been left untapped. Thanks to my dual credits received
              in high school, I was able to take classes I really wanted to take, such as Web Design and Interactive Media.

            </p>
            <a target="_blank" href="http://www.belmont.edu/" class="round-button" data-aos="flip-up" data-aos-once="true" data-aos-duration="700">Belmont University's site <i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></a>
